        "level": "h1"
      },
      "text": "PHP Connect to MySQL",
      "level": "h1"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "PHP 5 and later can work with a MySQL database using:",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">PHP 5 and later can work with a MySQL database using:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Earlier versions of PHP used the MySQL extension. However, this extension was deprecated in 2012.",
      "html": "<p class=\"intro\">Earlier versions of PHP used the MySQL extension. However, this \nextension was deprecated in 2012.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "Should I Use MySQLi or PDO?",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "If you need a short answer, it would be \"Whatever you like\".",
      "html": "<p>If you need a short answer, it would be \"Whatever you like\".</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Both MySQLi and PDO have their advantages:",
      "html": "<p>Both MySQLi and PDO have their advantages:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "PDO will work on 12 different database systems, whereas MySQLi will only work with MySQL databases.",
      "html": "<p>PDO will work on 12 different database systems, whereas MySQLi will only \nwork with MySQL databases.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "So, if you have to switch your project to use another database, PDO makes the process easy. You only have to change the connection string and a few queries. With MySQLi, you will need to rewrite the entire code - queries included.",
      "html": "<p>So, if you have to switch your project \nto use another database, PDO makes the process easy. You only have \nto change the connection string and a few queries. With MySQLi, you will need \nto rewrite the entire code - queries included.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Both are object-oriented, but MySQLi also offers a procedural API.",
      "html": "<p>Both are object-oriented, but MySQLi also offers a procedural API.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "Both support Prepared Statements. Prepared Statements protect from SQL injection, and are very important for web application security.",
      "html": "<p>Both support Prepared Statements. Prepared Statements protect \nfrom SQL injection, and are very important for web application security.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "MySQL Examples in Both MySQLi and PDO Syntax",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "In this, and in the following chapters we demonstrate three ways of working with PHP and MySQL:",
      "html": "<p>In this, and in the following chapters we demonstrate three ways of working \nwith PHP and MySQL:</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "metadata": {
        "level": "h2"
      },
      "text": "MySQLi Installation",
      "level": "h2"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "text": "For Linux and Windows: The MySQLi extension is automatically installed in most cases, when php5 mysql package is installed.",
      "html": "<p>For Linux and Windows: The MySQLi extension is automatically installed in \nmost cases, when php5 mysql package is installed.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "metadata": {},
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "\nhttp://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.installation.php",
          "href": "http://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.installation.php",
          "title": ""
        }
      ],
      "text": "For installation details, go to: http://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.installation.php",
      "html": "<p>For installation details, go to:\n<a href=\"http://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.installation.php\" target=\"_blank\">\nhttp://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.installation.php</a></p>"
